$PROB RUN# 0069 ; 0028 but THETA 7, THETA 8, OM7, OM8 estimated. $INPUT C STUD ID COHO SEX ROUT VISIT DOSE DV HALD INFDUR DAY TIME WGTB RACE HGTB AGE DIS MDV EVID AMT RATE ADDL II CMT $DATA ../183_6209_620_390.csv IGNORE=C IGNORE=(ID.EQ.91) ; 1015=91 in Study 183 is a placebo
$SUBROUTINES ADVAN4 TRANS4
$PK BWAVG = 76.5 ; kg. mean for the three studies,
MU_1=LOG(THETA(1)) TVCL=EXP(MU_1+ETA(1)) ; L/day
MU_7=LOG(THETA(7)) SBWCL=EXP(MU_7+ETA(7))
CL=TVCL*(WGTB/BWAVG)**SBWCL ; L/day
MU_2=LOG(THETA(2)) TVV2=EXP(MU_2+ETA(2)) ; L
MU_8=LOG(THETA(8)) SBWV2=EXP(MU_8+ETA(8))
V2=TVV2*(WGTB/BWAVG)**SBWV2 ; L
MU_3=LOG(THETA(3)) Q=EXP(MU_3+ETA(3)) ; L/day
MU_4=LOG(THETA(4)) V3=EXP(MU_4+ETA(4)) ; L
MU_5=LOG(THETA(5)) KA=EXP(MU_5+ETA(5)) ; 1/day
MU_6=LOG(THETA(6)/(1-THETA(6)) ) F1=1/(1+EXP(-(MU_6+ETA(6))) ) ; %
; calculate infusion rate for IV by infusion time and dose level IF( INFDUR.GT.0 ) R2=DOSE/INFDUR ; mg/day
S2=V2/1000 ; mg/L -> ng/mL
; "derived" K=CL/V2 K23=Q/V2 K32=Q/V3
; beta-phase exponential decay BETA=(K-(((K**2+(2*((K23*(K+K32))-(K*K32)))+K23**2+K32**2)**0.5)*( 1))+K23+K32)*0.5
; terminal half-life THAL=LOG(2)/BETA ; day
$ERROR DEL=0 IF (F.LE.0.0001) DEL=1 IPRE=F W1= 1 W2= F IRES= DV-IPRE IWRE=IRES/(W1+W2) Y = F + W1*ERR(1) + W2*ERR(2)

$SIGMA 0 FIXED ;[A] Additive 0.0320 ;[P] Proportional
;$EST METH=ITS INTERACTION PRINT=5 NITER=20 SIG=3 NOABORT MSFO=./0060.MSF $EST METH=1 INTERACTION PRINT=5 MAX=9999 SIG=3 NOABORT MSFO=./0069.MSF $EST METH=IMP INTERACTION PRINT=1 NITER=200 EONLY=0 NOABORT SIGL=9 CTYPE=3 MSFO=./0069.MSF $EST METH=IMP INTERACTION PRINT=1 NITER=10 ISAMPLE=2000 EONLY=1 NOABORT SIGL=9 MSFO=./0069.MSF
